Preparation<br>
From rack with barbell at upper chest height, position bar high on back of shoulders and grasp barbell to sides. Dismount bar from rack and stand with shoulder width stance.</p>

<p class="wb-stl-normal"><br>
Execution<br>
Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.</p>

<p class="wb-stl-normal"><br>
Common Mistakes<br>
1. Not going low enoug<br>
2. Leaning too far forward<br>
3. Rounding your back<br>
4. Incorrect knee and foot alignment<br>
5. Performing exercise too quickly</p>
